  "text": "Recently, similar CFTR-containing constructs have been published that differ in the size of the insert, and most important, in the assembly procedure. Kotzamanis et al. [CITATION_1] produced a CFTR-BAC of about 250 kb using a multistep recombination procedure that they carried out in E. coli, which used three BACs overlapping the CFTR locus. Thus the resulting molecules may not be representative of an authentic human CFTR locus. Although no data relating to the activity of the CFTR Cl À channel was provided, because of the presence of endogenous CFTR in their system, these authors demonstrated CFTR expression at the mRNA level in mouse cells. Clones containing integrated copies of BAC showed higher levels of human CFTR expression, probably due to copynumber variations, whereas episomal copies of their BAC, which were based on the oriP/EBNA1 element, showed lower levels of transcription with respect to the endogenous gene. [CITATION_2] CFTR expression from the human locus in BAC vectors C Auriche et al",
